abstract: Speaking at a prominent synagogue near Miami, the former New York City mayor spoke of his Jewish heritage and his support for Israel.
snippet: Speaking at a prominent synagogue near Miami, the former New York City mayor spoke of his Jewish heritage and his support for Israel.
lead_paragraph: AVENTURA, Fla. — Michael R. Bloomberg on Sunday addressed rising anti-Semitism and spoke personally of his Jewish heritage in a speech at a prominent synagogue near Miami, a sign that courting Jewish voters is core to his strategy of building support in Florida.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg on Sunday made his case for the presidency to fellow Jewish Americans, vowing not to revisit U.S. aid to Israel -- an approach that contrasts Bloomberg with several of his Democratic rivals, including his only fellow Jewish candidate in the race, Bernie Sanders.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg on Sunday made his case for the presidency to fellow Jewish Americans, vowing not to revisit U.S. aid to Israel -- an approach that contrasts Bloomberg with several of his Democratic rivals, including his only fellow Jewish candi...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Bloomberg on Sunday made his case for the presidency to fellow Jewish Americans, vowing not to revisit U.S. aid to Israel -- an approach that contrasts Bloomberg with several of his Democratic rivals, including his only fellow Jewish candidate in the race, Bernie Sanders.
headline_main: Bloomberg Vows Steadfast Commitment to US Aid for Israel

abstract: “We cannot run the risk of trying to defeat this president with the same Washington political warfare mentality that brought us to this point,” he said.
snippet: “We cannot run the risk of trying to defeat this president with the same Washington political warfare mentality that brought us to this point,” he said.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES — Picking up on a line of attack he first introduced Saturday, former Mayor Pete Buttigieg suggested to voters here, without naming him, that it would be too risky to nominate Senator Bernie Sanders to face off against President Trump.

abstract: “Folks grow up looking up to our sports heroes,” he said, before telling a story about Manchester United and his father.
snippet: “Folks grow up looking up to our sports heroes,” he said, before telling a story about Manchester United and his father.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES — Former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., said he was “shocked” about Kobe Bryant’s death, which he learned about after a campaign event at Maple Grove Elementary School here.
headline_main: Pete Buttigieg remembers Kobe Bryant as an ‘extraordinary athlete.’

abstract: On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the hill."
snippet: On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the h...
lead_paragraph: MASON CITY, Iowa — On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the hill."
headline_main: Biden's 'Consensus' Pitch Faces Biggest Test in Iowa
headline_print_headline: Biden's 'Consensus' Pitch Faces Biggest Test in Iowa

abstract: For all the gravity of a presidential impeachment trial, Americans don’t seem to be giving it much weight.
snippet: For all the gravity of a presidential impeachment trial, Americans don’t seem to be giving it much weight.
lead_paragraph: HAMBURG, Pa. — For all the gravity of a presidential impeachment trial, Americans don’t seem to be giving it much weight.
headline_main: In Divided America, Some Voters Tuning Out Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: In Divided America, Some Voters Tuning Out Impeachment Trial

abstract: Bernie Sanders was at 26 percent, Joe Biden at 25, Pete Buttigieg at 22 and Elizabeth Warren at 15 in a CBS News poll.
snippet: Bernie Sanders was at 26 percent, Joe Biden at 25, Pete Buttigieg at 22 and Elizabeth Warren at 15 in a CBS News poll.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A new CBS News poll released Sunday shows Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. neck-and-neck in Iowa eight days before the caucuses.

headline_main: Sanders and Biden are neck-and-neck in new Iowa poll.

abstract: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
snippet: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The entrepreneur Andrew Yang qualified for the next Democratic debate with a string of four strong polls released in quick succession on Saturday and Sunday.

headline_main: Andrew Yang qualifies for the next debate.

abstract: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
snippet: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
lead_paragraph: STORM LAKE, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg had one of northwest Iowa’s most coveted surrogates introduce him before a town-hall-style event Saturday night at Buena Vista University: David Johnson, a former state senator who in 2016 quit the Republican Party when Donald J. Trump won its presidential nomination.
headline_main: A Klobuchar endorser switches to Buttigieg? Not quite.
